Canopy Research is a comprehensive overview of these developments for explorers of this astonishing environment. The authors describe methods for reaching the canopy and the best ways to measure how the canopy, atmosphere, and forest floor interact. They address how to replicate experiments in challenging environments and lay the groundwork for creating standardized measurements in the canopy—essential tools for for understanding our changing world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aForest canopiesxResearchxMethodology. 0aForests and forestryxResearch. 7aNATURE / Ecology.2bisacsh  aanimals that live in trees.  abeauty of forests.  abiodiversity.  abiology.  abooks about birds.  abooks about the environment.  abooks for scientists.  aeasy to read.  aeducational books.  aengaging.  aenvironmental ecology.  aforest canopies.  aforest canopy research.  aforest evolution.  ahistory of forest.  ahome school science books.  ahow to study canopies.  ainformative books.  alearning from experts.  anative americans.  apage turner.  aplanet earth lovers.  aplant science.  aplants in biological science.  ascience lovers.  aunexplored environments.1 aFranklin, Jerry, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aSchowalter, Timothy, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052027371940uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095392540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520953925423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520953925/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY